<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Conger reports the receipt on the 16th instant of an unsatisfactory
                        edict decreeing exile for Tuan and Lan without capital sentence, suicide for
                        Chuang, death for Yü Hsien, degradation and imprisonment for Chao Shu-chiao
                        and Ying Men, and undetermined punishment for Chi Hsiu and Hsü
                        Cheng-yu.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>